gomodel:SYNGO_69  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using a PKC beta specific antibody and knockout control, it is demonstrated that PKC beta is expressed at the presynaptic terminal of the calyx of held.\n\n10/3/2017 Pim:\n-Literal: \"In slices from wild-type mice, antibody labeling for PKCα and PKCβ overlapped with vGlut1 labeling, consistent with presynaptic localization of these kinases at the calyx of Held synapse.\"\n-PCKalpha has C2 domain and is able to interact with lipids membranes. In previous annotations of this expert it was established that only a small fraction of the total PKC pool is membrane attached; the rest resides in the cytoplasm. Therefore, the \"cytosol\" component of the term is inferred. Because domain information is not reflected in GO, I agreed to this term.. Experimental description: In slices from wild-type mice, antibody labeling for PKCα and PKCβ overlapped with vGlut1 labeling, consistent with presynaptic localization of these kinases at the calyx of Held synapse." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_69" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

